Democratic Alliance (DA) leader Mmusi Maimane has announced the party’s premier candidate for Limpopo. He named provincial party leader Jacque Smalle. Smalle says his party is willing to serve. Meanwhile, Maimane  wants ANC leaders to be called to testify before the Zondo Commission on state capture. Maimane also wants action taken against municipal authorities who invested funds in the troubled VBS mutual bank. 